commit.message:
[#15] previousSetBit resets word length after miss (#16)

Currently it sets the length to the position of the needle in the first
word it looks up and only searches indices below that. This is incorrect
after the initial word where we need to search from the top.
guarantee that bits is non-null once resize has been called

[#7] Fix buggy handling around array boundaries (#13)

previousClearBit would return an incorrect value while previousSetBit
would miss everything if the index searched for was 2^16.

[#7] Implement previousClearBit and previousSetBit (#12)

Both methods essentially look up the desired bit and search linearly
backwards from that position. The allowed parameters and return values
match those of the JDK's BitSet.
Fixed a corner case bug with clear() (#10)
Static strategies, fixed bug with nextClearBit (#9)
